title: Texas is getting clubbed by TCU
text:
Texas is getting clubbed by TCU Resize Text 
TCU Coach Gary Patterson more or less said Texas stunk before Saturday’s game between his No. 4 Horned Frogs and the Longhorns. 
He’s right. Texas stinks. 
Here’s a summary: To recap Texas' first quarter: One turnover, one safety, one shanked punt, 0-4 on 3rd down, 20 total yards, zero points. Trails TCU, 30-0. 
— David Ubben (@davidubben) October 3, 2015 
Coach Charlie Strong is not long for his job at Texas. Even Fake Bo Pelini is kicking the tires. . @Longhorn_FB Do you offer a 401k plan 
— Fake Bo Pelini (@FauxPelini) October 3, 2015 
Seriously, this is bad. Texas is the fifth-most relevant CFB team in Texas at the moment, and that might even be a compliment. 
— Barrett Sallee (@BarrettSallee) October 3, 2015 
I mean … 
— SB Nation GIF (@SBNationGIF) October 3, 2015 Slow down, TCU! https://t.co/AIJPjDKQ2W
